                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/21/2003&nbsp;: 11:14:19 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Levels 10 and 11 are hard for necros.  12 is a huge improvement. So hunker down and grind through them.  The orc camps in EC are fun, but sometimes you can get more orcs than you can handle.  If this happens, have a plan in advance.  One technique is for you to assist the tank, send your pet, and Fear away the extra orcs.  They'll come back, and hate you.  When the orcs return, be watching, and Fear them away again.  Try to let the tank eat them one at a time. Ideally, you'd not be getting extra orcs of course.<br /><br />Try soloing in NRo.  Don't go in too deep until you're comfortable with it. Also, the guards will kill you so avoid the grassy area.  Enter NRo through the tunnel, and head to the pyramid to your right - it's a good base of operations.  At level 10 this zone is fun with a group.<br /><br /></span></font></td>
